		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://markos.gaivo.net/blog/?p=266#comment-140631</guid>
		<description>As it happens, I know I can do this, but I don&#039;t find this easy. And I hate profile manager with a passion.

You know what I would find easy? Having both versions installed and each used only parts of configuration or add-ons it can understand and leave rest the fuck alone, if it absolutely has to use the same configuration files. You know, like how browsers were supposed to handle HTML.

If you take a look at configuration files, as I did when I moved to FF3, it&#039;s quite obvious that developers themselves can&#039;t decide. E.g. signons.txt is different for each major version of Firefox, but other files in general aren&#039;t.</description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>As it happens, I know I can do this, but I don&#8217;t find this easy. And I hate profile manager with a passion.</p>
<p>You know what I would find easy? Having both versions installed and each used only parts of configuration or add-ons it can understand and leave rest the fuck alone, if it absolutely has to use the same configuration files. You know, like how browsers were supposed to handle HTML.</p>
<p>If you take a look at configuration files, as I did when I moved to FF3, it&#8217;s quite obvious that developers themselves can&#8217;t decide. E.g. signons.txt is different for each major version of Firefox, but other files in general aren&#8217;t.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
