		<description>well, I generally agree with your rant about multiple versions installed simultaneously, but if you only searched the web before installing you&#039;d find out that the trick is easy: install F3 into a different directory, run profile manager to create a new profile, edit shortcuts to run the desired version with the corresponding profile. Works on windows and linux.

I&#039;d switch to F3, but for the next few months I&#039;ll still have to develop for both. The browser test group just got another new member.</description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>well, I generally agree with your rant about multiple versions installed simultaneously, but if you only searched the web before installing you&#8217;d find out that the trick is easy: install F3 into a different directory, run profile manager to create a new profile, edit shortcuts to run the desired version with the corresponding profile. Works on windows and linux.</p>
<p>I&#8217;d switch to F3, but for the next few months I&#8217;ll still have to develop for both. The browser test group just got another new member.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
